The relationship between the **App** and **SystemErrorBoundary** components is defined by a hierarchical structure in which **SystemErrorBoundary** acts as a parent wrapper for the **App** component. In this configuration, **App** is rendered as a child component nested directly inside **SystemErrorBoundary**. Because **SystemErrorBoundary** invokes and renders **App**, the **App** component physically resides within **SystemErrorBoundary** in the application's stack trace.

This structural arrangement serves a specific functional purpose: providing error management at the root level of the application. By wrapping the **App** component, **SystemErrorBoundary** is able to catch and manage runtime errors that occur within **App**. This ensures that the application maintains error handling capabilities at its highest level, monitoring the execution of the nested **App** component.
